summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling all its relevant resolutions, particularly resolution 1524 of 30 January 2004, 
Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General of 14 July 2004, 
Recalling the conclusions of the Lisbon and Istanbul summits of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) 
regarding Abkhazia, Georgia, 
Recalling the principles contained in the Convention on the Safety of United Nations and Associated Personnel, 
Deploring the lack of identification of perpetrators of the shooting down of a UNOMIG helicopter on 8 October 2001, 
Stressing the unacceptable lack of progress on key issues of a comprehensive settlement of the conflict in Abkhazia, Georgia, 
Welcoming the positive momentum given to the peace process by high-level meetings of the Group of Friends in Geneva and 
Georgian-Russian summit meetings,
 Welcoming contributions made by UNOMIG and the CIS peacekeeping force, 
1. Reaffirms commitment to Georgia's sovereignty, independence and territorial integrity within its internationally recognized borders; 
2. Commends and supports the Secretary-General's efforts, assisted by the Russian Federation, Group of Friends and OSCE; 
3. Supports the document on "Basic Principles for the Distribution of Competences between Tbilisi and Sukhumi"; 
4. Regrets the Abkhaz side's refusal to discuss this document and urges consideration and constructive negotiations; 
5. Regrets lack of progress on political status negotiations and recalls that these documents facilitate meaningful negotiations; 
6. Calls on parties to overcome mutual mistrust and make concessions; 
7. Welcomes Georgia's commitment to a peaceful resolution and calls on both parties to dissociate themselves from militant rhetoric; 
8. Reminds all concerned to refrain from actions impeding the peace process; 
9. Welcomes regular meetings of senior representatives of the Group of Friends and United Nations in Geneva; 
10. Urges parties to participate actively in task forces and working groups; 
11. Encourages discussion on security guarantees; 
12. Calls on parties to take concrete steps to revitalize the peace process.
Here is a summarized version of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

13. Stresses the urgent need for progress on refugees and internally displaced persons, calls on both sides to display commitment to returns in close coordination with UNOMIG and consultations with UNHCR and the Group of Friends.
